All adult patients admitted in the ICU from September 2015 to March 2017 were considered eligible for the study. Patients admitted to the ICU for end-of-life care were excluded. In order to consider only the long-term ICU patients, those with an ICU length of stay shorter than 4 days were excluded from the analysis. Data abstraction forms were prospectively completed for all eligible patients. In particular, ENDING-S and SOFA scores were calculated daily from the ICU day 4 to the ICU discharge for each enrolled patient. In accordance with the previous paper [1], ENDING-S score was calculated as:
